                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Buy yourself a <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=14673" target="_blank" class="postlink">blue ceramic band</a> for 10-20pp in the bazaar.
<br />
Pacify room to your satisfaction and pull with this.
<br />
Aggro from it is so low, warrior can pull the mob off you just by breathing.
<br />
Tash (if you have resist issues) and slow.
<br />
Because Aggro is so easy to pass to the tank, you spend less mana rebuffing your rune.
<br />
I also use either Tepid Deeds or Forlorn Deeds, depending on the clerics mana, and the groups DPS.  If the mob is dying fast enough, the extra mana cost (225) of Forlorn is wasted.  And the shorter casting time of Tepid means it lands sooner, meaning the mob is slowed quicker.  With high DPS, this is actually more mana effecient for both you and the healer.
<br />
Since you're the puller/slower, mana management is paramount, as sitting around medding up for a round of Pacifications is time wasted.
<br />

<br />
Sierrae - Coercer - E'ci Server</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
