                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">...but the point is that it is ultra low aggro similar to casting Boggle for the single point of aggro.
<br />

<br />
If your guild is high enough to kill Ssra mobs, you can get the Hoop of Emptiness off of Archliche Rhag'Zhadune (AL).
<br />

<br />
MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM NO DROP
<br />
Slot: EAR
<br />
Charges: Unlimited
<br />
AC: 7
<br />
DEX: +6 CHA: +6 AGI: +9 HP: +80 MANA: +70
<br />
SV FIRE: +8 SV DISEASE: +8 SV COLD: +8 SV MAGIC: +8 SV POISON: +8
<br />
Required level of 55.
<br />
Effect: Nullify Magic (Must Equip, Casting Time: 5.0)
<br />
WT: 0.4 Size: SMALL
<br />
Class: CLR DRU SHM NEC WIZ MAG ENC
<br />
Race: ALL
<br />

<br />
No int on it kinda sucks, but I'm capped anyway =).  Good resists, some cha on it, great HP and Mana...and the effect.  I use it to pull at all times.  As long as someone at least swings at the mob when it comes into camp they will get the mob off of you.  Add that it will dispell a good chunk of any buffs a mob might have (bye bye, aego/virtue...or damage shield).  I have noticed I have to cast it twice on necro/wizards in LDoN missions to get rid of their DS.
<br />

<br />
I disagree with the use of a dot to pull as the MT may start pummeling the wrong mob if two or more come in by some fluke (the sand elves REALLY blend into the walls sometimes)...hard to control a dotted mob even if you only have to do it for a small amount of time.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
