                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hehehe I love pulling..under 2 conditions. 1. there is a pally in the group.  Most of the time they are quite cute, and they also have the nice stun to grab agro on and inc mob. 2. there is an alternate slower. (Shammys rock in this)
<br />

<br />
The reason I like pulling is simple.  If I pacy a room, I know which one to pull, and no nead for some bonehead melee to pull the wrong mob and pull agro on half the room =D.  Also If I make a mess with a resist or whatnot.. I clean it up (instead of cleaning up after the formentioned bonehead)  I pull using several diferent techniques.  I use root, pacy, mez, tash, slow, null magic, and scryers.  If there are 2 mobs in a room, I genraly root one and pull the other to the tank.  that gives the group a short time to kill first mob untill second is inc.  (works well with mez too, though mezed mob has a good chance of being blured into staying put)
<br />
I generaly like pulling with null magic.  I have had a mob jump on a tank without him/her even laying a hand on the mob before =D (mmmm might have to try this for a training strat  <img src="images/smiles/icon_twisted.gif" alt="icon_twisted.gif" border="0" />  JK =D
<br />

<br />
In a group lets say.... Pally, cleric, shammy, mage, chanter, monk.  Shammy slows, and I pull.  It works wonders.  Keeps me busy between buffs and I don't get all my mana drained by slowing.  
<br />

<br />
When you overpull, just mez adds and set them up for the kill.
<br />

<br />
Soulast Soulstar
<br />
Phantasmist of the 2nd Rank.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
